<H1>The <SAMP>hash</SAMP> command</H1>

<P>To monitor the progress of a transfer, it can be  useful  to
enter  the hash command before the transfer.  This instructs
ftp to print a `#' character for every 1024  bytes  of  data
received.  So long as a # appears every so often, the ftp is
still in progress, and there are no problems.</P>

<PRE WIDTH=80>   ftp&gt; <STRONG>hash</STRONG>
   Hash mark printing on (1024 bytes/hash mark).
   ftp&gt; <STRONG>get paper.txt</STRONG>
   200 PORT command okay.
   150 Opening data connection for paper.txt (0.50.50.54,1322).
   #################
   226 Transfer complete.
   16494 bytes sent in 0.98 seconds (16 Kbytes/s)
   ftp&gt;
</PRE>

<P>The file transferred in this  example  was  15788  bytes  in
length,  which  with communication overheads was transferred
in 16494 bytes. This causes 17 # marks to be printed.</P>

